* R&#x27;s statistics base-package implements the correlation coefficient with codice_1, or (with the P value also) with codice_2.
* The SciPy Python library via codice_3.
* The Pandas and Polars Python libraries implement the Pearson correlation coefficient calculation as the default option for the methods codice_4 and codice_5, respectively.
* Wolfram Mathematica via the codice_6 function, or (with the P value) with codice_7.
* The Boost C++ library via the codice_8 function.
* Excel has an in-built codice_9 function for calculating the Pearson&#x27;s correlation coefficient.

